<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-163-656  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 163 656.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 8 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Compuserve offers &quot;two for one&quot; starter kits in UK.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   CompuServe Forum (marketing).andO;Topic:     Computer industryUnited KingdomCompuServe Forum (Videotex System)Marketing StrategyPromotion of ProductOn-LineVideotex.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>COMPUSERVE OFFERS &quot;TWO FOR ONE&quot; STARTER KITS IN UK BRISTOL, ENGLAND, 1990 FEB07 (NB) -- As part of its plans to roll the service out in the UK, CompuserveForum, the European division of Compuserve, is offering two starter kits forthe price of one until further notice.andM;The kits price in at UKP 29-95 ($45) from Compuserve Forum's offices inBristol, and comprise a full ID and password for the service, plus a usermanual worth $15 and $25-worth of usage credit to the service.andM;The &quot;two for one&quot; idea is the brainchild of Andrew Gray, Compuserve Forum'sUK general manager.andP;  According to a spokesman for Compuserve Forum, the ideabehind the scheme is to allow individuals to get their friends online withthem, and companies to sign up for more than one account.andM;In a related story, Compuserve suffered an embarrassment last weekend whenits network access over Istel in the UK failed, for reasons unknown.andP;  Fromthe early hours of Saturday morning until midday on Monday, UK subscriberslogging on via Istel were greeted with a &quot;Call Disconnected&quot; message.andM;The break in service came just days after Compuserve Forum mailed its400-plus UK subscribers details of how to access the service via Istel.andO;According to a spokesman for Compuserve Forum, the customer support telephonelines were &quot;glowing red&quot; when the Bristol office staff returned to work onMonday morning.andM;(Steve Gold/19900207/Press andamp; Public Contact: Andrew Gray, Compuserve Forum -Tel: 0272-255111)</TEXT></DOC>